<doc id="201580" wikidata="Q4052248" url="?curid=201580" title="USS Macedonian">
<text>Two ships in the United States Navy have been named USS &quot;Macedonian&quot;. 

* The first was a 38-gun sailing frigate, originally of the Royal Navy, captured by Stephen Decatur in the War of 1812.
* The second was rebuilt from the keel of the first &quot;Macedonian&quot; and placed in service in 1836.</text><links>
